<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Woodchuck_Welmas" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Woodchuck_Welmas</a>

&quot;Philip J. Welmas was the name of a Native American professional football player in the early National Football League. He played in 4 games with the Oorang Indians for the 1923 season. He ended his professional career after the Indians disbanded in 1923. Woodchuck attended college and played college football at the Carlisle Indian School located in Carlisle, Pennsylvania.&quot;
